Footnote: should anyone wish to run the script themselves, the following diff is necessary because of slightly different `--help` output:
```diff
index 7c07a4f01..c3edac148 100755                                                                                                                               
--- a/hack/xref-helpmsgs-manpages
+++ b/hack/xref-helpmsgs-manpages
@@ -230,8 +230,8 @@ sub podman_help {                                                                                          
         #       ....
         #
         # Start by identifying the section we're in...
-        if ($line =~ /^Available\s+(Commands):/) {
-            $section = lc $1;
+        if ($line =~ /^(Available\s+)?(Commands):/) {
+            $section = lc $2;
         }
         elsif ($line =~ /^(Options):/) {
             $section = lc $1;
```

@edsantiago Your script did not find.
https://github.com/containers/podman/issues/15346
Might only be going one command deep, needs to be expanded to two levels?

For posterity. Diff:
```diff
diff --git a/hack/xref-helpmsgs-manpages b/hack/xref-helpmsgs-manpages
index de9ef8630..b9e4bd0ef 100755
--- a/hack/xref-helpmsgs-manpages
+++ b/hack/xref-helpmsgs-manpages
@@ -230,8 +230,8 @@ sub podman_help {                                                                                                                          
         #       ....
         #
         # Start by identifying the section we're in...
-        if ($line =~ /^Available\s+(Commands):/) {
-            $section = lc $1;
+        if ($line =~ /^(Available|Management\s+)?(Commands):/) {
+            $section = lc $2;
         }
         elsif ($line =~ /^(Options):/) {
             $section = lc $1;
```
Command:
```console
$ PODMAN=/usr/bin/docker hack/xref-helpmsgs-manpages 2>&1 | sed -ne 's/^.*podman \+\(.*\) --help. lists .\(.*\)., which is not.*/- [ ] docker \1 \2/p'
```
